---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title="About" description="About Aatman Mantri — backend engineer building distributed systems and cloud infrastructure." />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <h1>About</h1>

      <p>
        I'm a backend engineer who builds and operates production systems at scale.
        My work sits at the intersection of systems design, API performance, and cloud infrastructure.
      </p>

      <h2>What I Work On</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Distributed systems in Go</strong> — multi-service architectures with gateway patterns, hot/cold storage orchestration, and LRU caching</li>
        <li><strong>API performance in Python/Django</strong> — eliminating N+1 queries, multi-tier caching strategies, CTE-based query optimization</li>
        <li><strong>Kubernetes &amp; cloud infrastructure</strong> — Helm chart management, blue-green deployments, probe optimization, multi-cloud (GCP + Azure)</li>
        <li><strong>Medical imaging systems</strong> — DICOMweb servers, pathology viewing pipelines, large-scale image storage and retrieval</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Tech Stack</h2>
      <div class="tech-grid">
        <div class="tech-category">
          <h3>Languages</h3>
          <p>Go, Python, SQL</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tech-category">
          <h3>Frameworks</h3>
          <p>Django / DRF, FastAPI, Gin</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tech-category">
          <h3>Infrastructure</h3>
          <p>Kubernetes, Helm, Docker, GCP, Azure</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tech-category">
          <h3>Data</h3>
          <p>PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Redis</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>Philosophy</h2>
      <p>
        I believe the best backend code is the code you delete. Simplifying architectures — removing unnecessary
        dependencies, consolidating data stores, eliminating redundant abstractions — is often more valuable
        than building new features. Good systems are the ones that are easy to debug at 2 AM.
      </p>

      <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
      <p>
        Find me on <a href="https://github.com/AatmanMantri" target="_blank">GitHub</a>.
      </p>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  main {
    max-width: var(--max-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .tech-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .tech-category {
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1rem;
  }
  .tech-category h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }
  .tech-category p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }
  @media (max-width: 500px) {
    .tech-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
